  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Community Worker (Programme & Enterprise Lead)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Lead income generation projects, oversee the community learn and train initiative and collective involvement of residents in the public rental blocks communities.</li><li>Oversee and manage day-to-day operations for the social enterprise.</li><li>Collaborate with corporate and community partners and volunteers for resource mobilisation.</li><li>Drive marketing and sales efforts including digital, content creation and social media to grow visibility and engagement.</li><li>Manage budgeting, scheduling, monitoring, reporting and documentation across both programme and enterprise work.</li><li>Any other responsibilities or duties assigned.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>At least 3-5 years of experience in business development, marketing, social enterprise, or a related field.</li><li>Has a diploma or degree in Business, Marketing, Entrepreneurship or a related field.</li><li>Strong communication and relation-building skills.</li><li>Entrepreneurial and problem-solving mindset.</li><li>Proactive and hands-on professional with a proven ability to thrive in fast-paced environments and take initiative in problem-solving, event management, and on-the-ground support.</li><li>Digital and social media proficiency.</li><li>Willing and able to work during some weekday evenings and weekends.</li></ul>",
